This paper deals with the problem of synthesizing switching controllers for dynamical systems, which is a topic in control theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves the use of satisfiability-modulo theory (SMT) solvers, which are commonly used in automated reasoning and program synthesis, suggesting that cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.PL (Programming Languages) are also likely categories. The paper also discusses the use of counterexample-guided methods, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence, suggesting that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category. Finally, the paper deals with the synthesis of controllers for robotic systems, which suggests that cs.RO (Robotics) is a possible category as well.
